(In 2017, the van took them to Zero Base.)

785
00:28:29,450 --> 00:28:31,919
(From 2017 to 2019, this van always waited for Wanna One!)

786
00:28:31,920 --> 00:28:33,750
(In 2026, this van will take Wanna One back to 2017.)

787
00:28:33,920 --> 00:28:35,719
(This van and Wanna One go back years.)

788
00:28:35,720 --> 00:28:37,289
(Still, what are you doing here?)

789
00:28:37,290 --> 00:28:38,589
(They face the past memories.)

790
00:28:38,590 --> 00:28:39,590
(This has to be a dream.)

791
00:28:39,591 --> 00:28:41,660
(Amidst confusion caused by the van, two mysterious people appear.)

792
00:28:41,860 --> 00:28:44,259
What? What is he doing here?

793
00:28:44,260 --> 00:28:45,959
- What? - What is he doing here?

794
00:28:45,960 --> 00:28:47,630
- CEO Ko. - Sang Gil.

795
00:28:48,230 --> 00:28:49,970
(Familiar face number 1 from 2017)

796
00:28:51,230 --> 00:28:53,300
(Familiar face number 2 from 2017)

797
00:28:53,500 --> 00:28:55,870
(The identities of the men who look very familiar)

798
00:28:55,910 --> 00:28:58,879
(They assisted the group when they travelled abroad...)

799
00:28:58,880 --> 00:29:01,339
(and attended award ceremonies.)

800
00:29:01,340 --> 00:29:06,049
(They even appeared in "WANNA ONE GO: Zero Base.")

801
00:29:06,050 --> 00:29:08,989
(The two of them accompanied Wanna One for all schedules.)

802
00:29:08,990 --> 00:29:10,149
(Wanna One's manager, Sang Gil)

803
00:29:10,150 --> 00:29:11,350
(Wanna One's bodyguard, Dear Mister)

804
00:29:11,920 --> 00:29:13,660
What? There is Sang Gil!

805
00:29:14,060 --> 00:29:16,089
There is CEO Ko too.

806
00:29:16,090 --> 00:29:17,960
(We know both of them.)

807
00:29:18,360 --> 00:29:20,230
You need to get to work. Hurry over here.

808
00:29:20,460 --> 00:29:21,700
Are we leaving now?

809
00:29:22,170 --> 00:29:23,969
- Are we leaving as we are? - We need to leave. Hurry up.

810
00:29:23,970 --> 00:29:25,770
Everyone, let's say our final greeting.

811
00:29:25,970 --> 00:29:27,799
- Hold on. - The final greeting.

812
00:29:27,800 --> 00:29:29,940
(Despite confusion, they get into the official formation.)

813
00:29:30,470 --> 00:29:31,939
Everyone, this has been...

814
00:29:31,940 --> 00:29:34,439
- All I wanna do! Wanna One! - All I wanna do! Wanna One!

815
00:29:34,440 --> 00:29:36,010
- Thank you. - Thank you.

816
00:29:38,250 --> 00:29:39,350
Thank you.

817
00:29:40,280 --> 00:29:41,580
We're going now.

818
00:29:42,450 --> 00:29:43,720
(Let's meet again, Wannable.)

819
00:29:44,290 --> 00:29:46,119
- Kuan Lin. - Kuan Lin.

820
00:29:46,120 --> 00:29:47,489
- Kuan Lin. - Kuan Lin, let's go.

821
00:29:47,490 --> 00:29:48,590
Kuan Lin, let's go.

822
00:29:49,160 --> 00:29:50,330
What's this?

823
00:29:50,890 --> 00:29:52,259
- Sang Gil, what's this? - What's this?

824
00:29:52,260 --> 00:29:53,959
- Sang Gil. - It's me.

825
00:29:53,960 --> 00:29:55,130
(Entering the van naturally)

826
00:29:55,800 --> 00:29:57,330
(My goodness)

827
00:29:57,600 --> 00:29:58,600
Hello.

828
00:29:59,340 --> 00:30:00,370
Thank you.

829
00:30:00,740 --> 00:30:01,910
CEO Ko, hello.

830
00:30:02,070 --> 00:30:04,770
(I can't believe I'll ride this van again.)

831
00:30:04,970 --> 00:30:06,109
What's this?

832
00:30:06,110 --> 00:30:08,850
(WANNA ONE GO: Back to Base is extraordinary from the start.)

833
00:30:09,010 --> 00:30:10,780
I thought there was an accident.

834
00:30:10,980 --> 00:30:12,280
This completes Wanna One.

835
00:30:12,680 --> 00:30:13,980
- I can't believe it. - Sit here.

836
00:30:14,520 --> 00:30:15,889
(The van's destination finally gets revealed!)

837
00:30:15,890 --> 00:30:16,890
(Let's go!)

838
00:30:16,891 --> 00:30:18,219
(Isn't this place too big?)

839
00:30:18,220 --> 00:30:19,889
(It has been upgraded!)

840
00:30:19,890 --> 00:30:23,959
(Which place makes the members exclaim nonstop?)

841
00:30:23,960 --> 00:30:25,960
(I don't want to leave.)

842
00:30:26,530 --> 00:30:28,129
- Let's go! - Let's hit the road!

843
00:30:28,130 --> 00:30:29,600
It feels like 2017.

844
00:30:29,900 --> 00:30:32,240
The van feels very comfortable since it has been a while.

845
00:30:32,840 --> 00:30:33,840
It makes me sleepy.

846
00:30:34,140 --> 00:30:36,709
Didn't we always pass out in the van back in the days?

847
00:30:36,710 --> 00:30:38,139
- Yes, we did. - Whenever we woke up,

848
00:30:38,140 --> 00:30:39,680
we were someplace new.

849
00:30:39,910 --> 00:30:42,250
Sang Gil, how does it feel to drive Solati again?

850
00:30:42,750 --> 00:30:43,750
My back hurts.

851
00:30:43,750 --> 00:30:44,750
(Laughing)

852
00:30:44,880 --> 00:30:47,119
Sang Gil is wearing makeup.

853
00:30:47,120 --> 00:30:48,949
- Really? Are you wearing makeup? - I'm not wearing makeup.

854
00:30:48,950 --> 00:30:50,649
I'm wearing sunscreen.

855
00:30:50,650 --> 00:30:51,890
(Our manager is cute.)

856
00:30:52,090 --> 00:30:53,719
Are we going to do the Try Not to Laugh Challenge?

857
00:30:53,720 --> 00:30:55,389
- We can't. - I have no confidence.

858
00:30:55,390 --> 00:30:57,229
- We won't be funny. - It won't be as funny as it was.

859
00:30:57,230 --> 00:30:58,230
To be honest, I have no confidence.

860
00:30:58,231 --> 00:31:00,259
Unless we can make it funnier than it was back then...

861
00:31:00,260 --> 00:31:01,829
- I can't do that. - I can't do that either.

862
00:31:01,830 --> 00:31:04,300
- Unless we can do that... - I'll need to take off my pants.

863
00:31:04,400 --> 00:31:05,869
(It was legendary.)

864
00:31:05,870 --> 00:31:08,569
Now that we're adults, we should drink beer.

865
00:31:08,570 --> 00:31:09,609
That sounds great.

866
00:31:09,610 --> 00:31:11,939
Most of us were underage back then. But we're adults now.

867
00:31:11,940 --> 00:31:13,609
- But there is a problem. - What is it?

868
00:31:13,610 --> 00:31:14,809
When Dae Hwi is drunk...

869
00:31:14,810 --> 00:31:16,510
- Come on! - Maybe we should exclude Dae Hwi.

870
00:31:16,580 --> 00:31:18,720
(Shh! Dae Hwi is a professional idol.)

871
00:31:18,880 --> 00:31:20,750
Where on earth are we going?

872
00:31:21,020 --> 00:31:23,889
Didn't we go to Japan on the same day back then?

873
00:31:23,890 --> 00:31:24,989
That's right.

874
00:31:24,990 --> 00:31:26,019
We didn't even get to shower.

875
00:31:26,020 --> 00:31:27,819
That's right. We didn't even get to shower.

876
00:31:27,820 --> 00:31:30,259
- They loved surprises too much. - That's right.

877
00:31:30,260 --> 00:31:31,429
Are we going to the Incheon International Airport?

878
00:31:31,430 --> 00:31:33,129
I just saw a road sign for it.

879
00:31:33,130 --> 00:31:35,029
We're passing the Gwangmyeong Station.

880
00:31:35,030 --> 00:31:37,299
- West Seoul? - West Seoul.

881
00:31:37,300 --> 00:31:39,199
- Now, we get suspicious first. - I know.

882
00:31:39,200 --> 00:31:40,870
- After all, we don't know anything. - I know.

883
00:31:41,200 --> 00:31:42,209
Where are we going?

884
00:31:42,210 --> 00:31:44,010
We don't know where we're going.

885
00:31:44,540 --> 00:31:46,640
It's very exciting since we don't know the destination.

886
00:31:47,310 --> 00:31:48,479
(The mysterious destination is nearby!)

887
00:31:48,480 --> 00:31:50,349
We're going deeper inside.

888
00:31:50,350 --> 00:31:52,749
- It's big. - Gosh, it's so big.

889
00:31:52,750 --> 00:31:55,050
- It's Wanna Base, right? - It's Wanna Base.

890
00:31:55,320 --> 00:31:56,549
- Come this way. - It's here.

891
00:31:56,550 --> 00:31:57,889
Everyone, come this way.

892
00:31:57,890 --> 00:31:59,059
- My goodness. - Wanna Base.

893
00:31:59,060 --> 00:32:00,089
- What? - What?

894
00:32:00,090 --> 00:32:01,289
- My goodness. - Wanna Base.

895
00:32:01,290 --> 00:32:02,889
- What? It's Wanna Base. - It's the vending machine.

896
00:32:02,890 --> 00:32:04,129
Is it the vending machine?

897
00:32:04,130 --> 00:32:06,260
I love it!

898
00:32:08,330 --> 00:32:11,130
(Kang Daniel's message has arrived.)

899
00:32:12,270 --> 00:32:15,170
Wannable! I haven't said that in a long while.

900
00:32:16,610 --> 00:32:19,809
All of us were working hard separately.

901
00:32:19,810 --> 00:32:22,380
We have many memories...

902
00:32:23,050 --> 00:32:25,450
we can revisit with fondness.

903
00:32:26,920 --> 00:32:29,520
It's so nice that we can come together again.

904
00:32:29,690 --> 00:32:31,990
Don't get hurt. Good luck at the training center.

905
00:32:32,220 --> 00:32:35,560
- All I wanna do! Wanna One! Yes! - All I wanna do! Wanna One! Bye!

906
00:32:35,590 --> 00:32:36,960
It's a relief.

907
00:32:37,430 --> 00:32:41,400
Unfortunately, I won't be able to join the show this time.

908
00:32:41,760 --> 00:32:45,440
It's because of my military service, so please be understanding.

909
00:32:46,240 --> 00:32:48,569
Please give a lot of love to WANNA ONE GO.

910
00:32:48,570 --> 00:32:50,139
(Kang Daniel)

911
00:32:50,140 --> 00:32:51,210
Bye.

912
00:32:51,440 --> 00:32:53,440
(Salute. Let's meet again soon.)

913
00:32:53,680 --> 00:32:55,880
(February 9, 2026, the day Kang Daniel entered the military)

914
00:32:56,380 --> 00:32:59,619
Today is the day I enter the military,

915
00:32:59,620 --> 00:33:01,450
so I'm going to the Nonsan Training Center.

916
00:33:01,480 --> 00:33:02,850
I'll come back safely.

917
00:33:05,590 --> 00:33:09,159
If you stay put,

918
00:33:09,160 --> 00:33:12,660
I'll come back and show...

919
00:33:12,930 --> 00:33:16,069
my diligent and cool self as an idol...

920
00:33:16,070 --> 00:33:18,370
like I've promised.

921
00:33:18,840 --> 00:33:20,699
Let's meet again when my hair grows back.

922
00:33:20,700 --> 00:33:21,740
Bye.

923
00:33:22,040 --> 00:33:24,940
(You can see the next episode right away!)
